.TH "" "1" "April 2026" "0.1.0"
.SH "NAME"
\fB\fR
.P
delta(1) \-\- CLI client for the delta productivity platform
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBdelta\fP [\fB\-\-json\fP [fields]] [\fB\-\-jq\fP expr] [\fB\-q\fP|\fB\-\-quiet\fP] [\fB\-\-no\-color\fP] [\fB\-\-server\fP url] [\fB\-\-debug\fP] <command> [args] [flags] [filters]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBdelta\fR is a command\-line interface for managing tasks, calendar events,
.br
categories, automations, and integrations on the delta productivity platform\. It
.br
communicates with a delta server over HTTPS\.
.P
The CLI follows a noun\-verb grammar: \fBdelta <noun> <verb> [args] [\-\-flags] [filters]\fP\|\. Flags are used for writes, filters for reads\.
.P
Running \fBdelta\fP with no arguments is equivalent to \fBdelta task list\fP, showing
.br
pending tasks sorted by urgency\.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS delta task
.P
Task CRUD and status changes\. Running \fBdelta task\fP with no verb defaults to
.br
\fBdelta task list\fP\|\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task list\fP [\fB\-\-from\fP date] [\fB\-\-until\fP date] [filters]:
.br
List tasks\. Accepts filter expressions and date range flags\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task add\fP description [flags]:
.br
Create a new task\. The description is a positional argument (quote multi\-word
.br
strings)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task edit\fP id [flags]:
.br
Update fields on an existing task\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task done\fP id\.\.\.:
.br
Mark one or more tasks as complete\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task delete\fP id\.\.\.:
.br
Soft\-delete (cancel) one or more tasks\. Bulk deletes require \fB\-y\fP or
.br
interactive confirmation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task wip\fP id\.\.\.:
.br
Set one or more tasks to wip status\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task block\fP id\.\.\.:
.br
Set one or more tasks to blocked status\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task pending\fP id\.\.\.:
.br
Set one or more tasks to pending status\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task dep add\fP id depends\-on\-id:
.br
Add a dependency between two tasks\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task dep rm\fP id depends\-on\-id:
.br
Remove a dependency between two tasks\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta task dep list\fP id:
.br
List dependencies for a task\.

.RE
.SS Task add/edit flags

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-due\fP date:
.br
Due date\. Accepts natural language (see DATE FORMATS) or ISO 8601\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-category\fP name:
.br
Category name\. Categories are created implicitly\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-p\fP, \fB\-\-priority\fP n:
.br
Priority level\. 0 = none, 1+ = ascending urgency\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-start\fP datetime:
.br
Start time\. Creates a calendar event when used with \fB\-\-end\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-end\fP datetime:
.br
End time for calendar events\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-all\-day\fP:
.br
Mark as an all\-day event\. Use with \fB\-\-due\fP (date only, no time)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-recurrence\fP text:
.br
Recurrence rule\. Accepts NLP text (e\.g\. "every monday") or raw RRULE\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-recur\-mode\fP mode:
.br
Recurrence mode: \fBscheduled\fP or \fBcompletion\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-location\fP text:
.br
Location string\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-meeting\fP url:
.br
Meeting URL\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-notes\fP text:
.br
Plain text notes\. Pass \fB\-\fP to read from stdin\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-status\fP status:
.br
Initial status (default: pending)\.

.RE
.SS Task edit\-only flags

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-scope\fP scope:
.br
Recurrence edit scope: \fBthis\fP, \fBfuture\fP, or \fBall\fP\|\. Required when editing a
.br
recurring task\. In interactive mode the CLI prompts if omitted; in
.br
non\-interactive mode it errors\.

.RE
.SS delta cat

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cat\fP:
.br
List all categories with their task counts\.

.RE
.SS delta cron
.P
Manage scheduled automations\. Running \fBdelta cron\fP with no verb defaults to
.br
\fBdelta cron list\fP\|\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron list\fP:
.br
List all automations\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron add\fP [flags]:
.br
Create an automation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron edit\fP id [flags]:
.br
Update an automation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron delete\fP id:
.br
Delete an automation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron run\fP id:
.br
Trigger an automation manually\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron enable\fP id:
.br
Enable a disabled automation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta cron disable\fP id:
.br
Disable an automation\.

.RE
.SS Cron add/edit flags

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-name\fP name:
.br
Automation name\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-schedule\fP cron\-expr:
.br
Cron expression (e\.g\. "0 9 * * 1" for every Monday at 9am)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-type\fP type:
.br
Recipe type: \fBgithub_issues\fP, \fBwebhook\fP, or \fBcustom\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-config\fP json:
.br
JSON configuration blob\. Pass \fB\-\fP to read from stdin\.

.RE
.SS delta auth
.P
Authentication commands\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth login\fP:
.br
Start device flow authentication\. Opens a browser URL and waits for
.br
confirmation\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth login \-\-token\fP:
.br
Paste an API token directly (for headless/CI environments)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth logout\fP:
.br
Clear stored credentials from keyring and credentials file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth status\fP:
.br
Show the current authenticated user and auth method\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth token\fP:
.br
Display the current API token\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta auth token regenerate\fP:
.br
Regenerate the API token (invalidates the previous token)\.

.RE
.SS delta feed
.P
iCal subscription management\. Running \fBdelta feed\fP with no verb shows the current subscription
.br
URL or status\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta feed generate\fP:
.br
Generate or regenerate the iCal subscription URL\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta feed revoke\fP:
.br
Revoke the current subscription URL\.

.RE
.SS delta import

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta import\fP file\.ics [\fB\-\-category\fP name]:
.br
Import events from an iCal file\. Optionally assign all imported events to a
.br
category\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta import taskwarrior\fP export\-file:
.br
Import tasks from a Taskwarrior JSON export\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta import pending\fP export\-file:
.br
Import tasks from a pending\.nvim export\.

.RE
.SS delta export

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta export\fP [\fB\-\-from\fP date] [\fB\-\-until\fP date] [filters]:
.br
Export tasks and events as iCal to stdout\. Redirect to save:
.br
\fBdelta export > calendar\.ics\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta export \-\-id\fP id:
.br
Export a single event as iCal\.

.RE
.SS delta config
.P
Settings management\. Running \fBdelta config\fP with no verb shows all settings\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta config get\fP key:
.br
Get the value of a setting\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta config set\fP key value:
.br
Set a setting value\.

.RE
.P
Valid keys: \fBdefault\-view\fP, \fBshow\-completed\fP, \fBurgency\-weights\fP,
.br
\fBgeo\-provider\fP\|\.
.SS delta integration

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta integration list\fP:
.br
List configured integrations\. Running \fBdelta integration\fP with no verb
.br
defaults to list\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta integration test\fP provider:
.br
Test an integration's API key validity\.

.RE
.SS delta invite
.P
Invite link management\. Running \fBdelta invite\fP with no verb defaults to
.br
\fBdelta invite list\fP\|\.

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta invite list\fP:
.br
List invite links\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta invite create\fP:
.br
Generate a new invite link\.

.RE
.SS delta share

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta share\fP task\-id:
.br
Generate or show the share link for a task\.

.RE
.SS delta completion

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta completion bash\fP:
.br
Output bash shell completion script\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta completion zsh\fP:
.br
Output zsh shell completion script\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta completion fish\fP:
.br
Output fish shell completion script\.

.RE
.P
Install example: \fBdelta completion zsh > ~/\.zfunc/_delta\fP
.SS delta help

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta help\fP:
.br
Show overview and command cheatsheet\. If running in a terminal and the man
.br
page is installed, opens \fBman delta\fP instead\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta help filters\fP:
.br
Show filter syntax reference\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta help dates\fP:
.br
Show date format reference\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta help auth\fP:
.br
Show authentication setup walkthrough\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdelta help examples\fP:
.br
Show workflow recipes and usage examples\.

.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.P
Universal flags accepted by every command:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP:
.br
Show help for the current command\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-json\fP [fields]:
.br
Output as JSON\. Optionally pass a comma\-separated list of fields to include\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-jq\fP expr:
.br
Filter JSON output with a jq expression (implies \fB\-\-json\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP:
.br
Quiet mode\. Print only IDs on list commands, nothing on success for mutations\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-no\-color\fP:
.br
Disable colored output\. Also respected via the \fBNO_COLOR\fP environment
.br
variable\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-server\fP url:
.br
Override the server URL\. Also settable via \fBDELTA_SERVER\fP environment variable
.br
or the config file\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-\-debug\fP:
.br
Print HTTP requests and responses to stderr\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\-y\fP, \fB\-\-yes\fP:
.br
Skip confirmation prompts for destructive bulk operations\.

.RE
.SH FILTERS
.P
Filters use \fBkey:value\fP syntax and are passed as positional arguments to list
.br
commands\. Date\-type keys support \fB\|\.before\fP and \fB\|\.after\fP modifiers\.
.SS Filter keys

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBstatus\fP:value:
.br
Filter by task status\. Values: \fBpending\fP, \fBwip\fP, \fBdone\fP, \fBblocked\fP,
.br
\fBcancelled\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBcategory\fP:name:
.br
Filter by category name\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBpriority\fP:n:
.br
Filter by priority level\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdue\fP:date, \fBdue\.before\fP:date, \fBdue\.after\fP:date:
.br
Filter by due date, or tasks due before/after a date\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBcreated\.before\fP:date, \fBcreated\.after\fP:date:
.br
Filter by creation date\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBupdated\.before\fP:date, \fBupdated\.after\fP:date:
.br
Filter by last\-updated date\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBsort\fP:field:
.br
Sort results\. Fields: \fBurgency\fP (default), \fBdue\fP, \fBcreated\fP, \fBpriority\fP\|\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlimit\fP:n:
.br
Maximum number of results to return\.

.RE
.SS Date range shorthand
.P
The \fB\-\-from\fP and \fB\-\-until\fP flags on \fBdelta task list\fP and \fBdelta export\fP are
.br
shorthand for date ranges on \fBstartAt\fP:
.RS 2
.nf
delta task list \-\-from monday \-\-until friday
.fi
.RE
.SH DATE FORMATS
.P
All date and datetime flags accept the following formats:
.SS Relative dates

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBtoday\fP, \fBtomorrow\fP, \fByesterday\fP
.IP \(bu 2
Day names: \fBmonday\fP, \fBtuesday\fP, \fBwednesday\fP, \fBthursday\fP, \fBfriday\fP, \fBsaturday\fP,
.br
\fBsunday\fP (refers to the next occurrence)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBeow\fP (end of week), \fBeom\fP (end of month)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBnext week\fP, \fBnext month\fP

.RE
.SS Offset syntax

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB+3d\fP (3 days from now)
.IP \(bu 2
\fB+1w\fP (1 week from now)
.IP \(bu 2
\fB+2m\fP (2 months from now)

.RE
.SS ISO 8601

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
Date: \fB2026\-04\-01\fP
.IP \(bu 2
Datetime: \fB2026\-04\-01T09:00:00\fP

.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
.SS Config file
.P
Location: \fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/delta/config\.toml\fP (default: \fB~/\.config/delta/config\.toml\fP)
.P
Example:
.RS 2
.nf
server = "https://delta\.barrettruth\.com"
.fi
.RE
.SS Precedence
.P
Configuration values are resolved in order of decreasing priority:

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
Command\-line flags (\fB\-\-server\fP, \fB\-\-json\fP, etc\.)
.IP \(bu 2
Environment variables (\fBDELTA_SERVER\fP, \fBDELTA_TOKEN\fP, \fBNO_COLOR\fP)
.IP \(bu 2
Config file
.IP \(bu 2
Built\-in defaults

.RE
.SS Environment variables

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBXDG_CONFIG_HOME\fP:
.br
Base directory for config files (default: \fB~/\.config\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBXDG_DATA_HOME\fP:
.br
Base directory for data files including credentials (default: \fB~/\.local/share\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBDELTA_SERVER\fP:
.br
Server URL (default: \fBhttps://delta\.barrettruth\.com\fP)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBDELTA_TOKEN\fP:
.br
API token\. Highest\-priority auth method\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBNO_COLOR\fP:
.br
When set (any value), disables colored output\.

.RE
.SS Auth token storage
.P
Token precedence (highest to lowest):

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fBDELTA_TOKEN\fP environment variable
.IP \(bu 2
OS keyring (macOS Keychain, GNOME Keyring, KDE Wallet)
.IP \(bu 2
\fB$XDG_DATA_HOME/delta/credentials\.json\fP (default: \fB~/\.local/share/delta/credentials\.json\fP, permissions 0600)

.RE
.SH EXIT CODES

.RS 1
.IP \(bu 2
\fB0\fP:
.br
Success\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB1\fP:
.br
Runtime or unknown error\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB2\fP:
.br
Usage or validation error (bad arguments, missing required flags)\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB3\fP:
.br
Resource not found\.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB4\fP:
.br
Unauthorized (missing or invalid credentials)\.

.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic task operations
.P
Create a task with a due date and category:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task add "Buy groceries" \-\-due tomorrow \-\-category personal
.fi
.RE
.P
Complete a task:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task done 5
.fi
.RE
.P
Set multiple tasks to wip:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task wip 3 7 12
.fi
.RE
.P
Edit a task's priority and due date:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task edit 5 \-\-priority 2 \-\-due friday
.fi
.RE
.P
Delete (cancel) a task:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task delete 5
.fi
.RE
.SS Filtering tasks
.P
List tasks in a category:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list category:work
.fi
.RE
.P
List high\-priority tasks due before end of week:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list priority:2 due\.before:eow
.fi
.RE
.P
List tasks created in the last week, sorted by due date:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list created\.after:\-7d sort:due
.fi
.RE
.P
List tasks for a date range:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list \-\-from monday \-\-until friday status:pending
.fi
.RE
.SS Calendar events
.P
Create an event with start and end times:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task add "Team standup" \-\-start "2026\-04\-01T09:00" \-\-end "2026\-04\-01T09:30" \-\-category work
.fi
.RE
.P
Create an all\-day event:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task add "Company holiday" \-\-due 2026\-04\-01 \-\-all\-day
.fi
.RE
.P
Create a recurring event:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task add "Weekly review" \-\-start "monday 10:00" \-\-end "monday 11:00" \-\-recurrence "every monday"
.fi
.RE
.P
Edit a single instance of a recurring task:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task edit 15 \-\-due tomorrow \-\-scope this
.fi
.RE
.SS Piping and scripting
.P
Get IDs of completed tasks and delete them:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list \-q status:done | xargs delta task delete \-y
.fi
.RE
.P
JSON output for scripting:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list \-\-json id,description,status
.fi
.RE
.P
Filter JSON with jq:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta task list \-\-json \-\-jq '\.[]\.description'
.fi
.RE
.P
Export calendar to file:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta export \-\-from today \-\-until +2w > next\-two\-weeks\.ics
.fi
.RE
.SS Auth setup
.P
Interactive device flow login:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta auth login
.fi
.RE
.P
Token\-based login for CI:
.RS 2
.nf
$ export DELTA_TOKEN="your\-api\-token"
$ delta task list
.fi
.RE
.P
Or paste a token directly:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta auth login \-\-token
.fi
.RE
.P
Check auth status:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta auth status
.fi
.RE
.SS Configuration
.P
Set the server URL:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta config set server https://delta\.barrettruth\.com
.fi
.RE
.P
View all settings:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta config
.fi
.RE
.SS Automations
.P
Create a cron job:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta cron add \-\-name "Sync GitHub issues" \-\-schedule "0 9 * * 1" \-\-type github_issues \-\-config '{"repo": "barrettruth/delta"}'
.fi
.RE
.P
List automations:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta cron list
.fi
.RE
.P
Trigger an automation manually:
.RS 2
.nf
$ delta cron run 1
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.P
Project: https://github.com/barrettruth/delta
.P
Web interface: https://delta.barrettruth.com
